# AI Agent Development Rules

## Provider Abstraction

All AI provider calls (OpenAI, Google Gemini, Anthropic) must go through `packages/ai-core`. Never import provider SDKs directly in application code.

```typescript
// Correct — use ai-core abstraction
import { createCompletion, AgentConfig } from '@uvidai/ai-core';

// Wrong — direct SDK usage in app code
import OpenAI from 'openai'; // ❌
```

## Agent Configuration

Temperature, model, and provider are configurable per agent type. Define agent configs as typed objects:

```typescript
import { z } from 'zod';

export const agentConfigSchema = z.object({
  provider: z.enum(['openai', 'gemini', 'anthropic']),
  model: z.string(),
  temperature: z.number().min(0).max(2),
  maxTokens: z.number().positive(),
  systemPromptPath: z.string(),
});

export type AgentConfig = z.infer<typeof agentConfigSchema>;
```

## Prompt Management

- Store all agent prompts as markdown files in `docs/prompts/`.
- Name prompt files descriptively: `location-analyst.md`, `legal-checker.md`, `lifestyle-scorer.md`.
- Load prompts at runtime — never hardcode prompt text in source code.
- Prompts can include template variables using `{{variableName}}` syntax, replaced at runtime.

```
docs/prompts/
  location-analyst.md      — Main location analysis agent
  legal-checker.md         — APR/cadastre legal status checker
  lifestyle-scorer.md      — Walkability and lifestyle scoring
  eco-context.md           — Environmental analysis prompt
  summarizer.md            — Multi-source result summarizer
```

## Tool / Function Definitions

- Every tool that an AI agent can call must have a Zod schema defining its parameters.
- Tool implementations must validate inputs against the schema before execution.
- Tool results must be typed with a response schema.

```typescript
import { z } from 'zod';

export const searchNearbyToolSchema = z.object({
  latitude: z.number().min(-90).max(90),
  longitude: z.number().min(-180).max(180),
  radiusMeters: z.number().min(100).max(10000),
  category: z.enum(['school', 'kindergarten', 'healthcare', 'pharmacy', 'transit', 'park']),
});

export type SearchNearbyParams = z.infer<typeof searchNearbyToolSchema>;
```

## Streaming Responses

Follow Vercel AI SDK patterns for streaming:

```typescript
import { streamText } from 'ai';

const result = streamText({
  model: getModel(agentConfig),
  system: loadPrompt('location-analyst'),
  messages,
  tools: registeredTools,
});

return result.toDataStreamResponse();
```

## Cost Tracking

Every AI call must record usage data. Log the following to the `ai_usage` table:

| Field | Description |
|---|---|
| `provider` | openai, gemini, anthropic |
| `model` | Specific model identifier |
| `input_tokens` | Prompt/input token count |
| `output_tokens` | Completion/output token count |
| `latency_ms` | Round-trip time in milliseconds |
| `agent_type` | Which agent made the call |
| `user_id` | Requesting user (nullable for system calls) |
| `session_id` | Conversation session identifier |

```typescript
await this.usageService.record({
  provider: config.provider,
  model: config.model,
  inputTokens: usage.promptTokens,
  outputTokens: usage.completionTokens,
  latencyMs: endTime - startTime,
  agentType: 'location-analyst',
  userId: context.userId,
  sessionId: context.sessionId,
});
```

## Message Logging

All AI request/response pairs must be logged to the `messages` table:

- Store the full message history for each conversation session.
- Include the role (`system`, `user`, `assistant`, `tool`).
- Store tool calls and their results.
- Redact any PII before logging if applicable.

## Error Handling

- Wrap all AI calls in retry logic with exponential backoff.
- Handle provider-specific errors (rate limits, content filters, context length exceeded).
- Fall back to an alternative provider/model when the primary is unavailable.
- Never expose raw AI provider errors to the end user — map to user-friendly messages.

```typescript
try {
  return await this.aiCore.complete(config, messages);
} catch (error) {
  if (isRateLimitError(error)) {
    return await this.aiCore.complete(fallbackConfig, messages);
  }
  throw new InternalServerErrorException('AI service temporarily unavailable');
}
```

## Data Connectors Integration

When an AI agent needs external data, it must call through `packages/data-connectors`:

- APR business data → `@uvidai/data-connectors/apr`
- Spatial/cadastre data → `@uvidai/data-connectors/geosrbija`
- Air quality → `@uvidai/data-connectors/sepa`
- Points of interest → `@uvidai/data-connectors/osm`

Never make raw HTTP calls to external APIs from agent code.

## Testing AI Code

- Unit test tool definitions with mock AI responses.
- Test Zod schemas with edge-case inputs.
- Integration test full agent flows with recorded/mocked provider responses.
- Snapshot test prompt templates to catch unintended changes.
